<section class="section about-section" id="about">
  <div class="container about-inner">
    <div class="about-img-wrap">
      <img
        src="/images/Headshot.jpeg"
        alt="Jacob Gordon — JG Concrete"
        class="about-headshot"
      />
      <div class="about-credential">
        <img
          src="/images/CMI_Icon.png"
          alt="Concrete Industry Management — Texas State University"
          class="cim-logo"
        />
        <span>CIM Graduate — Texas State</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="about-text">
      <h2>Hi, I'm Jacob Gordon</h2>
      <p>
        Owner of JG Concrete. I graduated from Texas State University's
        Concrete Industry Management program — one of the only dedicated
        concrete degrees in the country — and started this business because
        I wanted DFW homeowners to have a contractor they could actually
        rely on.
      </p>
      <p>
        When you hire JG Concrete, you're getting someone who understands
        concrete at every level — the mix, the prep, the pour, and the
        finish. I know the DFW heat, soil movement, and heavy use can tear
        apart a poorly done driveway or patio fast, so I make sure yours
        is built to handle all of it.
      </p>
      <p>
        Your driveway isn't just a slab. It's where your kids shoot hoops,
        where your car sits every day, and where you need a surface that
        won't crack, sink, or fall apart after a few seasons. That's why
        I take every job seriously — right mix, right prep, right process.
        Concrete that holds up for years.
      </p>
      <a href="#quote" class="btn btn-primary">Get a Free Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
